yout-grid-align:none;\r\n\ttext-autospace:none;\r\n\tfont-size:20.0pt;\r\n\tmso-bidi-font-size:13.0pt;\r\n\tfont-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n\tmso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\r\n\tmso-fareast-language:ZH-CN;}\r\np.MsoPlainText, li.MsoPlainText, div.MsoPlainText\r\n\t{margin:0in;\r\n\tmargin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n\tmso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n\tfont-size:11.0pt;\r\n\tmso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;\r\n\tfont-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n\tmso-fareast-font-family:SimSun;\r\n\tmso-bidi-font-family:\"Courier New\";\r\n\tmso-fareast-language:ZH-CN;}\r\n /* Page Definitions */\r\n@page\r\n\t{mso-page-border-surround-header:no;\r\n\tmso-page-border-surround-footer:no;}\r\n@page Section1\r\n\t{size:8.5in 11.0in;\r\n\tmargin:.25in .25in .25in .25in;\r\n\tmso-header-margin:.5in;\r\n\tmso-footer-margin:.5in;\r\n\tmso-page-numbers:1;\r\n\tmso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.Section1\r\n\t{page:Section1;}\r\n-->\r\n</style>\r\n</head>\r\n\r\n<body lang=EN-US style='tab-interval:.5in;text-justify-trim:punctuation'>\r\n\r\n<div class=Section1>\r\n\r\n<h3>OPERATING SYSTEMS PRINCIPLES</h3>\r\n\r\n<h1>Lubomir F. Bic, Alan C. Shaw</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2>Contents </h2>\r\n\r\n<h1>1 Introduction</h1>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>1.1 The Role of Operating Systems <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>1.1.1 Bridging the Hardware/ Application Gap<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>1.1.2 Three Views of Operating Systems<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>1.2 Organization of Operating Systems<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>1.2.1 Structural Organization<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>1.2.2 The Hardware Interface <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>1.2.3 The Programming Interface <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>1.2.4 The User Interface <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>1.2.5 Runtime Organization. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>1.3 Operating System Evolution and Concepts<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>1.3.1 Early Systems <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>1.3.2 Batch Operating Systems <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>1.3.3 Multiprogramming Systems. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>1.3.4 Interactive Operating Systems <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>1.3.5 Personal Computer and Workstation Operating Systems<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>1.3.6 Real-Time Operating Systems<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>1.3.7 Distributed Operating Systems<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Part One Process Management and Coordination </h2>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal>2 Basic Concepts: Processes and Their Interactions </p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>2.1 The Process Notion <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>2.2 Defining and Instantiating Processes <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>2.2.1 Precedence Relations Among Processes <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>2.2.2 Implicit Process Creation. 44 <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>2.2.3 Explicit Process Creation with fork and join <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>2.2.4 Process Declarations and Classes <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>2.3 Basic Process Interactions <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>2.3.1 Competition: The Critical Section Problem <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>2.3.2 Cooperation. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>2.4 Semaphores <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>2.4.1 Semaphore Operations and Data <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>2.4.2 Mutual Exclusion with Semaphores <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>2.4.3 Semaphores in Producer/Consumer Situations <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>2.5 Event Synchronization<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h1>3 Higher-Level Synchronization and Communication</h1>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoPlainText style='margin-left:.5in'>3.1 Shared Memory Methods</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoPlainText style='margin-left:1.0in'>3.1.1 Monitors </p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoPlainText style='margin-left:1.0in'>3.1.2 Protected Types </p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoPlainText style='margin-left:.5in'>3.2 Distributed Synchronization\r\nand Communication</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoPlainText style='margin-left:1.0in'>3.2.1 Message-Based\r\nCommunication</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoPlainText style='margin-left:1.0in'>3.2.2 Procedure-Based\r\nCommunication</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoPlainText style='margin-left:1.0in'>3.2.3 Distributed Mutual\r\nExclusion</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoPlainText style='margin-left:.5in'>3.3 Other Classic\r\nSynchronization Problems</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoPlainText style='margin-left:1.0in'>3.3.1 The Readers/Writers\r\nProblem</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoPlainText style='margin-left:1.0in'>3.3.2 The Dining Philosophers\r\nProblem</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoPlainText style='margin-left:1.0in'>3.3.3 The Elevator Algorithm</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoPlainText style='margin-left:1.0in'>3.3.4 Event Ordering with\r\nLogical Clocks</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>4 The Operating System Kernel: Implementing Processes and Threads</h1>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoPlainText style='margin-left:.5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>4.1 Kernel Definitions and Objects<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoPlainText style='margin-left:.5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>4.2 Queue Structures <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoPlainText style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>4.2.1 Resource Queues in an Operating System<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoPlainText style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>4.2.2 Implementations of Queues<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoPlainText style='margin-left:.5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>4.3 Threads<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoPlainText style='margin-left:.5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>4.4 Implementing Processes and Threads<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoPlainText style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>4.4.1 Process and Thread Descriptors<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoPlainText style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>4.4.2 Implementing Operations on Processes<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoPlainText style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>4.4.3 Operations on Threads<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoPlainText style='margin-left:.5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>4.5 Implementing Synchronization and Communication\r\nMechanisms<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoPlainText style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>4.5.1 Semaphores and Locks<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoPlainText style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>4.5.2 Monitor Primitives<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=MsoPlainText style='margin-left:1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n\"Times New Roman\"'>4.5.3 Clock and Time